        <presentation>
          <material>
            <mattext texttype="text/html">&lt;div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SVG group elements&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; ("g") have no visual presence but they help us to group elements and to apply transformations to multiple elements in one step. Select &lt;strong&gt;all&lt;/strong&gt; the answers that describe the following line of code correctly:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;lt;g class="x-axis axis" transform="translate(0,400)"&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/g&amp;gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</mattext>
          </material>
          <response_lid ident="response1" rcardinality="Multiple">
            <render_choice>
              <response_label ident="93084">
                <material>
                  <mattext texttype="text/plain">The code specifies an empty SVG group with the classes “axis” and “x-axis”</mattext>
                </material>
              </response_label>
              <response_label ident="39115">
                <material>
                  <mattext texttype="text/plain">The transform attribute shifts the g element 400 pixels down</mattext>
                </material>
              </response_label>
              <response_label ident="93253">
                <material>
                  <mattext texttype="text/plain">The transform attribute defines the drawing space (400 x 400px) in the g element</mattext>
                </material>
              </response_label>
              <response_label ident="78643">
                <material>
                  <mattext texttype="text/plain">The code specifies an SVG group</mattext>
                </material>
              </response_label>
            </render_choice>
          </response_lid>
        </presentation>
